title: [TensorFlow.org] Anchor Tag Incorrect Reference
body_html:
Nothing really serious but I noticed the link on see Pip installation for Windows on getting started doc body is using an anchor separated with dashes #pip-installation-on-windows while the corresponding id uses underscores #pip_installation_on_windows.

For instance, the body anchor (which works on github)
#pip-installation-on-windows
and the right side nav-bar Index link, working normally, with underscores
#pip_installation_on_windows

I was going to submit a PR but changing to the latter breaks on github.

body:
Nothing really serious but I noticed the link on `see Pip installation for Windows` on getting started doc body is using an anchor separated with dashes `#pip-installation-on-windows`  while the corresponding `id` uses underscores `#pip_installation_on_windows`.

For instance, the body anchor (which works on github) 
`#pip-installation-on-windows` 
and the right side nav-bar `Index` link, working normally, with underscores
`#pip_installation_on_windows`

I was going to submit a PR but changing to the latter breaks on github.
